The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph classes, which are typically studied in the areas of graph theory and algorithms. The problem of finding large induced subgraphs is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has been extensively studied in the literature. The paper proposes a subexponential time algorithm for this problem, which is a significant result in the area of algorithm design. The paper also uses techniques from parameterized algorithms, which is a subfield of algorithms that has gained significant attention in recent years. Based on these observations, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
